Shelley G. Broader  CEO, President & Director, Chico's FAS, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 3 Board Members in 3 different organizations across 10 different industries.See Board Relationships52$9,463,751As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Ms. Shelley G. Broader has been the Chief Executive Officer and President at Chico's FAS Inc. since December 1, 2015. Ms. Broader served as the President and Chief Executive Officer of Walmart EMEA at Wal-Mart Stores Inc. from June 1, 2014 to October, 2015. She served as the Chief Executive Officer and President at Walmart Canada Corp., a subsidiary of Walmart Canada Corp. since September 28, 2011 and January 19, 2012 respectively. She has 25 years of North American ... retail leadership experience, where she served as Senior Vice President at the Wal-Mart's Sam's Club division. She served as the President of Crafts Chain Michael's. She served as the Chief Operating Officer and President of Michaels Stores, Inc. from June 2008 to September 2009. She served as the Chief Merchandising Officer at Walmart Canada Corp. since December 2010. She served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of Sweetbay LLC from February 23, 2006 to June 9, 2008. From June 2003 to March 2006, she served as the President and Chief Operating Officer of Sweetbay LLC. Ms. Broader also served as the President and Chief Operating Officer at Sweetbay Supermarket Inc. from June 23, 2003 to June 2008. From April 1991 to June 2003, she served at various positions of increasing management responsibility at Hannaford Bros. Co. Inc., including Senior Vice President of Business Strategy, Marketing and Communications. Her prior financial service industry experience includes Massachusetts Financial Services Company and Assistant Vice President at First Albany Corporation. She has been a Director of Chico's FAS Inc. since December 1, 2015. She has been Non Executive Independent Director at Raymond James Financial, Inc. since 2008. She serves as a Member of Canadian Advisory Board at Catalyst Inc. She served as a Director at Wal-Mart de Mexico SAB De CV since March 2011. She served as a Non-Executive Director of Massmart Holdings Limited from July 16, 2014 to November 9, 2015. She served as a Trustee of St. Leo University. She served as a Member of Board of Advisors of H. Lee Moffitt Cancer Center & Research Institute. She served as a Director of United Way of Tampa Bay. Ms. Broader obtained a Bachelor of Arts degree from Washington State University.Read Full Background




